      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To adjust your inventory turnover ratio, you first need to adjust your Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) to reflect the missing stock; essentially, you add the value of the lost shrinkage to standard COGS.  Next, calculate your Average Inventory after factoring in that missing stock value. Finally, divide the adjusted COGS by the adjusted Average Inventory to get your true, though perhaps alarming, adjusted turnover ratio. This will show how much more potential inventory movement you've lost to theft or decay.",
